WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:02.830
♪♪

00:04.420 --> 00:05.250
Bex:
Previously on Andi Mack...

00:05.250 --> 00:07.040
I need someone
to do my math homework.

00:07.040 --> 00:08.500
I have a moral code.

00:08.500 --> 00:09.710
People cheat
all the time.

00:09.710 --> 00:11.290
You need
to go talk to Coleman.

00:11.290 --> 00:12.460
About what?

00:12.460 --> 00:14.420
I kind of told him
that you did my homework.

00:14.420 --> 00:16.420
I'm suspended
from the basketball team.

00:16.420 --> 00:18.290
That's so unfair.

00:18.290 --> 00:20.830
Jonah's taking me
to the trampoline park
tomorrow!

00:20.830 --> 00:23.210
You're really
the coolest girl
I've ever known.

00:23.210 --> 00:25.250
I'm really enjoying
all the compliments.

00:25.250 --> 00:28.500
Andi, I'm going to camp
for eight weeks.

00:28.500 --> 00:30.210
I'm just a little sad.

00:30.210 --> 00:32.420
-But it's all
gonna work out.
-Maybe it will.

00:34.420 --> 00:36.080
He'll be back
before you know it.

00:36.080 --> 00:38.380
I could say the same thing
about you and Pops.

00:38.380 --> 00:43.080
Until he gets back,
AndiShack can be your
cozy home away from home.

00:43.080 --> 00:45.960
-Is that spot taken?
-Bring it in.

00:48.420 --> 00:50.500
(whispers)
Bex, I love you.

00:53.210 --> 00:54.460
Say it again.

00:55.500 --> 00:56.420
I'm gonna marry Bowie.

00:56.420 --> 00:58.420
(screams)
Wait.

00:58.420 --> 01:00.040
He asked you
without me?

01:00.040 --> 01:03.330
-I'm gonna ask him.
-We're gonna ask him?

01:06.580 --> 01:09.250
♪ ♪

01:17.330 --> 01:18.920
-Basic.
-Hmm.

01:20.830 --> 01:21.960
Flashy.

01:22.960 --> 01:23.960
Ooh.

01:25.500 --> 01:26.500
No skulls.

01:27.500 --> 01:28.830
Hmm?

01:28.830 --> 01:30.460
No snakes.

01:31.580 --> 01:35.540
Is there even such a thing
as an engagement ring
for a man?

01:35.540 --> 01:38.080
Well, we're not looking
for an engagement ring
for a man.

01:38.080 --> 01:40.710
We're looking
for an engagement ring
for a Bowie.

01:41.710 --> 01:42.750
Which is what?

01:42.750 --> 01:44.620
We'll know
when we see it.

01:44.620 --> 01:45.670
(both sigh)

01:45.670 --> 01:47.080
Okay, last tray.

01:48.540 --> 01:49.710
(sighs)

01:49.710 --> 01:52.670
-You see anything?
-Nope.

01:52.670 --> 01:55.960
-Me neither.
-Are you willing
to reconsider skulls?

01:55.960 --> 01:57.330
There are
some nice ones.

02:00.580 --> 02:02.330
♪ ♪

02:04.460 --> 02:05.710
I kinda like this one.

02:08.460 --> 02:11.500
-The yin-yang.
-What is it?

02:12.500 --> 02:14.880
It's the world
in perfect balance.

02:14.880 --> 02:18.580
It's the Chinese symbol
for the universe.

02:18.580 --> 02:19.580
(gasps)

02:23.080 --> 02:24.380
It's the ring.

02:26.080 --> 02:28.040
(both scream)

02:28.040 --> 02:29.500
(theme music playing)

02:29.500 --> 02:32.460
♪ I'm standing on the edge ♪

02:32.460 --> 02:35.250
♪ And everything I kno-o-ow ♪

02:35.250 --> 02:37.000
♪ Has blown away ♪

02:38.500 --> 02:42.000
♪ Life is upside down ♪

02:42.000 --> 02:44.580
♪ But any way it go-o-oes ♪

02:44.580 --> 02:46.670
♪ I'll work it out ♪

02:48.080 --> 02:51.500
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

02:51.500 --> 02:53.790
♪ Here we go ♪

02:55.210 --> 02:56.500
♪ One, two, three! ♪

02:56.500 --> 02:58.540
♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

02:58.540 --> 03:00.790
♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪

03:00.790 --> 03:03.120
♪ There ain't no map to follow

03:03.120 --> 03:05.670
♪ But I'm with you all the way

03:05.670 --> 03:08.080
-♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪
-♪ Hey! ♪

03:08.080 --> 03:09.960
-♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪
-♪ Hey! ♪

03:09.960 --> 03:12.540
-♪ There ain't no map
to follow ♪
-♪ Hey! ♪

03:12.540 --> 03:14.460
♪ But I'm with you all the way

03:14.460 --> 03:15.670
♪ Hey! ♪

03:15.670 --> 03:17.920
♪ All the way ♪

03:17.920 --> 03:20.710
Cyrus: Ooh, that's the way.
Let's see you take it
to the hole.

03:20.710 --> 03:24.120
She's going for the trey.
She's all the way downtown!

03:24.120 --> 03:27.710
Ooh, so close. So close.

03:27.710 --> 03:30.250
Go for the bucket.
Baby needs a bucket.

03:30.250 --> 03:33.790
Cyrus! Stop talking.

03:33.790 --> 03:35.250
You don't like my patter?

03:35.250 --> 03:36.710
I thought it sounded
pretty good.

03:36.710 --> 03:38.790
I watched an entire
basketball game.

03:38.790 --> 03:40.330
It went on forever.

03:40.330 --> 03:42.500
(scoffs) It's just me here.

03:42.500 --> 03:43.620
I don't need patter.

03:43.620 --> 03:45.620
But there's a basketball game
on Friday,

03:45.620 --> 03:48.120
and the Slayer is back in town!

03:48.120 --> 03:50.460
Ooh! I can use that
in my patter.

03:50.460 --> 03:55.460
Say a prayer, 'cause here
comes the Slayer!

03:55.460 --> 03:57.040
You won't need it then either.

03:59.750 --> 04:01.500
I'm not rejoining the team.

04:02.540 --> 04:04.670
-Is this because of TJ?
-No.

04:04.670 --> 04:07.120
You think he's not gonna pass
you the ball, but he will.

04:07.120 --> 04:09.960
Buffy, he's a completely
different person.

04:11.170 --> 04:13.290
He got a "C"
on a math test.

04:13.290 --> 04:15.080
-He did?
-You should've seen him.

04:15.080 --> 04:17.500
It was so cute.
He was running around,
showing everybody.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.540
He was like a little puppy
who passed a math test.

04:19.540 --> 04:21.750
He's still a puppy
I don't want to play with.

04:23.670 --> 04:24.830
(sighs)

04:24.830 --> 04:28.290
Okay. We have the ring!

04:28.290 --> 04:30.250
We're proposing tonight.

04:30.250 --> 04:32.830
Oh, we can't.
We don't have a plan.

04:32.830 --> 04:35.670
We need a plan.
Okay, what's the plan?

04:35.670 --> 04:39.040
Ugh. My pizza delivery idea
was so good,

04:39.040 --> 04:41.540
and it was
totally wasted on you.

04:41.540 --> 04:45.790
-No, it wasn't.
-We didn't even
eat the pizza.

04:45.790 --> 04:47.750
Okay. We'll do it
right this time.

04:47.750 --> 04:49.670
(gasps)
How about a cake?

04:49.670 --> 04:54.500
A cake is delicious.
Where do we put the ring?

04:54.500 --> 04:57.790
Inside the cake!
And then we mark
where it is,

04:57.790 --> 05:00.170
so it ends up in the slice
that we serve to Bowie.

05:00.170 --> 05:02.750
You are on fire today!

05:02.750 --> 05:04.750
(laughs)
Every day.

05:04.750 --> 05:06.920
Oh. Someone
feeling herself?

05:06.920 --> 05:08.920
(gasps)
I got it.

05:08.920 --> 05:11.040
-I got the idea!
-Tell me. Tell me.

05:11.040 --> 05:14.040
We drop in on Bowie
at the Red Rooster.

05:14.040 --> 05:15.960
-Right now?
-Why not?

05:15.960 --> 05:18.960
Okay, yeah,
we were just
in the neighborhood.

05:18.960 --> 05:21.420
Chat, chat, chat,
and then we say,

05:21.420 --> 05:23.420
"Hey, what are you doing
for dinner tomorrow night?"

05:23.420 --> 05:25.710
"Come over. We'll order in."

05:25.710 --> 05:29.250
(gasps) That's good.
We'll order in like
it's super no big deal!

05:29.250 --> 05:31.710
Okay, okay, but we have
to keep it very low-key,

05:31.710 --> 05:33.670
super cazh.
Can you do that?

05:33.670 --> 05:36.460
I can. The question is, can you?

05:36.460 --> 05:38.580
(scoffs)
Please, I'm an expert.

05:38.580 --> 05:41.460
Look at this.
Straight face.

05:41.460 --> 05:42.620
Let's see yours.

05:43.710 --> 05:45.960
Not bad!
But can you hold it?

05:45.960 --> 05:48.750
Hold what?
I'm not holding anything.

05:48.750 --> 05:51.830
-This is just my face.
-That's great!

05:51.830 --> 05:55.000
Okay, the most important thing
is we can't let Bowie know
that we're up to something.

05:55.000 --> 05:59.580
(both laughing)

06:02.080 --> 06:03.670
You two are up
to something.

06:03.670 --> 06:05.500
-Both: No, we're not.
-Wha?

06:07.500 --> 06:09.960
(both giggle, shush)

06:20.420 --> 06:21.500
Ring.

06:25.750 --> 06:26.790
Toothpick.

06:31.290 --> 06:32.500
Frosting.

06:36.960 --> 06:38.120
Yum.

06:38.120 --> 06:40.210
Shall we close her up?

06:47.000 --> 06:48.830
Please check
the toothpick
is secure.

06:49.880 --> 06:51.250
The toothpick is secure.

06:53.000 --> 06:57.080
-Looking good!
-It's gonna be the cake
that takes the cake.

06:57.080 --> 06:59.000
-(both chuckle)
-Whoa!

06:59.000 --> 07:00.620
Who trashed the kitchen?

07:02.460 --> 07:05.330
If this is what happens
when we bake one cake,

07:05.330 --> 07:08.750
how are we gonna make
an entire meal?

07:08.750 --> 07:12.540
I say we walk away
and use CeCe's kitchen
to make dinner.

07:12.540 --> 07:14.790
(gasps)
And we serve it
in her dinning room,

07:14.790 --> 07:16.920
on her really nice dishes
that match.

07:16.920 --> 07:19.830
And let animated
forest animals
take care of all this.

07:19.830 --> 07:20.830
-(sighs)
-Andi: Hmm.

07:23.330 --> 07:24.540
Mm-hmm.

07:34.290 --> 07:36.170
What are
we doing here?

07:36.170 --> 07:39.040
I just gotta grab
something outta my locker.
I'll be right back.

07:45.620 --> 07:47.380
(basketball bounces)

07:54.330 --> 07:57.330
Well, well,
if it isn't Jock-iavelli.

07:57.330 --> 07:59.920
Don't hurt your brain
trying to figure it out.

07:59.920 --> 08:02.790
Machiavelli,
evil Italian politician.

08:02.790 --> 08:06.080
-Lucky guess.
-Hey, if it makes you
feel any better,

08:06.080 --> 08:08.540
I got a two-game suspension
for you doing my homework.

08:08.540 --> 08:10.750
That's does
make me feel better.

08:10.750 --> 08:13.170
-I'm back on the team now.
-Good for you.

08:13.170 --> 08:16.000
-But I hear
you're not coming back.
-Why do you care what I do?

08:16.000 --> 08:19.120
Well, 'cause you're good.
I mean, not as good as me,

08:19.120 --> 08:22.040
-but pretty good.
-(scoffs) I'm not
as good as you?

08:22.040 --> 08:23.620
And you know that how?

08:23.620 --> 08:26.170
If you thought you were,
you'd be coming back
to the team.

08:26.170 --> 08:28.000
What's the game here, TJ?

08:28.000 --> 08:30.830
You're trying
to make me mad. Why?

08:30.830 --> 08:32.830
Hey, guys,
what's going on?

08:32.830 --> 08:34.960
You gonna play
some one-on-one
or some thing?

08:34.960 --> 08:36.250
(whispers)
We aren't there yet, Cyrus.

08:36.250 --> 08:37.500
(whispers)
Oh, sorry.

08:37.500 --> 08:39.960
I assume those are
my gym clothes.

08:39.960 --> 08:41.170
Great.

08:41.170 --> 08:42.750
It's on.

08:44.750 --> 08:47.580
(sighs)
That was
a pathetic ambush.

08:48.830 --> 08:50.580
This is why
I wanted to rehearse.

08:56.750 --> 08:59.000
I can't believe
you got me a hotel room.

08:59.000 --> 09:01.790
Well, I can't believe you
were sleeping in AndiShack.

09:01.790 --> 09:03.710
It was just for one night.

09:03.710 --> 09:06.960
I get it.
The house is lonely
without Pops.

09:06.960 --> 09:09.880
-You need
a change of scenery.
-(sighs)

09:11.420 --> 09:13.960
-Where am I going?
-How does a suite

09:13.960 --> 09:16.500
with room service
at the Barclay sound?

09:16.500 --> 09:19.000
(chuckles)
Out of your price range.

09:19.000 --> 09:21.170
Let me worry about that
when Dad gets the bill.

09:21.170 --> 09:22.960
Does it have a spa?

09:22.960 --> 09:25.620
You will be wrapped
in seaweed within the hour.

09:26.880 --> 09:29.960
You know, I think this
is exactly what I need.

09:29.960 --> 09:33.170
It is!
Now hurry up and relax.

09:33.170 --> 09:36.040
(laughs)
Look at me being
all spontaneous.

09:36.040 --> 09:38.420
I should plan
to do this more often.

09:41.790 --> 09:44.960
♪ ♪

09:52.000 --> 09:54.040
Ooh, these are
some nice pots.

09:54.040 --> 09:56.460
I'm developing
a new appreciation for pots.

09:56.460 --> 09:59.330
-Let's use them all.
-(chuckles)

10:05.000 --> 10:08.080
-Shoot for ball?
-No, you take it

10:08.080 --> 10:11.120
and enjoy it,
because once I get it,

10:11.120 --> 10:13.420
-you're not gonna see it again.
-You're pretty confident

10:13.420 --> 10:16.710
for a guy who's...
usually pretty confident.

10:16.710 --> 10:18.500
-Let's just start.
-Make it, take it.

10:18.500 --> 10:20.040
First to seven,
win by two.

10:21.250 --> 10:23.790
Yeah, I was gonna keep score,
but you lost me already.

10:23.790 --> 10:26.920
Listen, I'm not gonna
hold back.

10:26.920 --> 10:30.620
I'm gonna play at my game,
and if you can't keep up--

10:30.620 --> 10:32.250
-(rock music playing)
-(crowd cheering)

10:32.250 --> 10:33.420
That's one.

10:40.040 --> 10:41.420
Oh, hey, Coach!

10:45.580 --> 10:46.920
That's two.

10:46.920 --> 10:48.750
♪ Stay hungry, stay thirsty ♪

10:48.750 --> 10:50.210
♪ Don't be afraid
to get down and dirty ♪

10:50.210 --> 10:52.170
♪ Stay hungry,
stay thirsty ♪

10:52.170 --> 10:54.420
♪ Don't be afraid
to get down and dirty ♪

10:56.120 --> 10:58.080
The chicken is done.

10:58.080 --> 11:00.380
How many of these
am I shucking?

11:00.380 --> 11:01.380
Shuck 'em all.

11:02.750 --> 11:05.040
All right,
so we got the chicken.
What else?

11:05.040 --> 11:10.120
We have potatoes,
risotto, soup, asparagus...

11:10.120 --> 11:11.460
Ear de corn.

11:11.460 --> 11:14.500
Garlic bread,
Caesar salad,
and cheese plate.

11:14.500 --> 11:17.170
(sighs)
Is it too much food?

11:17.170 --> 11:19.000
I hope he saves
room for cake.

11:19.000 --> 11:21.380
That's right.
And we made a cake.

11:21.380 --> 11:24.040
-I thought we couldn't cook.
-Turns out we were just lazy.

11:25.670 --> 11:29.080
(rock music playing)

11:35.040 --> 11:38.790
♪ I work much harder
than all of the competition ♪

11:38.790 --> 11:42.710
♪ I put my sight on the prize,
now I'm addicted ♪

11:42.710 --> 11:46.210
♪ Some imitators and haters
wish they could get this ♪

11:46.210 --> 11:49.540
♪ They can't
imagine my passion,
I'm never finished ♪

11:49.540 --> 11:51.080
♪ Study hard,
get'cho lesson ♪

11:51.080 --> 11:53.080
♪ Whatever goes down,
don't take no mess ♪

11:53.080 --> 11:54.830
♪ You done
already beat the rest ♪

11:54.830 --> 11:56.880
♪ What's one more round?
You still the best ♪

11:56.880 --> 11:58.750
♪ That's what
my momma told me ♪

11:58.750 --> 12:00.670
♪ Get me ready
for the competition ♪

12:00.670 --> 12:02.250
♪ I go hard
and nobody can hold me ♪

12:02.250 --> 12:04.040
♪ Just like my momma said ♪

12:04.040 --> 12:07.920
♪ She say I came from a line
of winners before me ♪

12:07.920 --> 12:11.620
♪ She told me
slay every challenger
at the door, see ♪

12:11.620 --> 12:15.210
♪ So I set a bar up so high,
it's outta your reach ♪

12:15.210 --> 12:19.000
♪ I sit back and watch you try,
you'll never beat me... ♪

12:19.000 --> 12:20.830
-I'm about to win.
-Lol.

12:20.830 --> 12:23.210
-You played
a pretty good game.
-Not over yet.

12:23.210 --> 12:24.920
Yes, it is.

12:29.210 --> 12:33.880
(laughs, mimics explosion)
I win!

12:33.880 --> 12:36.710
-(Buffy laughs)
-You won?

12:36.710 --> 12:38.790
You won!
I knew you would win!

12:38.790 --> 12:41.580
-You won!
-♪ That's what
my momma told me ♪

12:41.580 --> 12:43.330
♪ Get me ready
for the competition ♪

12:43.330 --> 12:45.040
♪ When I'm ready,
ain't nobody can go with me ♪

12:45.040 --> 12:47.080
♪ Cuz they can't match
my precision ♪

12:47.080 --> 12:48.620
♪ Study hard,
get'cho lesson ♪

12:48.620 --> 12:50.580
♪ Whatever goes down,
don't take no mess ♪

12:50.580 --> 12:52.210
♪ That's what
my momma said ♪♪

12:52.210 --> 12:57.080
"Nice game, TJ.
You played hard."
"Oh, thank you, TJ."

12:57.080 --> 13:00.670
-It really was a good game.
-First one-on-one I ever lost.

13:00.670 --> 13:04.210
So my beautiful
if under-rehearsed
plan worked!

13:04.210 --> 13:08.000
-What was that?
-To prove that you and TJ
could play basketball together.

13:08.000 --> 13:09.920
And you did.
And you won!

13:09.920 --> 13:12.670
Not that anyone needs
to know that.

13:12.670 --> 13:16.290
And now, no more
nonsense about you
not rejoining the team.

13:16.290 --> 13:18.120
You're definitely
rejoining the team.

13:19.170 --> 13:20.920
(chuckles)
No, I'm not.

13:20.920 --> 13:23.420
You're just gonna quit
playing basketball?

13:23.420 --> 13:28.290
(sighs) Of course not.
I'm still going to play.

13:28.290 --> 13:31.710
-I don't get it.
-Is there some other team
we don't know about?

13:31.710 --> 13:34.460
I didn't want
to say anything
until it was official,

13:34.460 --> 13:36.040
but I just got permission.

13:37.380 --> 13:39.500
I'm starting
a girls' basketball team.

13:41.380 --> 13:42.580
That's a brilliant plan...

13:42.580 --> 13:45.210
-(laughs)
-...which eclipses
even my brilliant plan.

13:45.210 --> 13:47.580
Driscoll, you got moves.

13:47.580 --> 13:49.080
Thank you.

13:49.080 --> 13:51.290
♪ ♪

13:55.500 --> 13:56.750
Are you nervous?

13:58.330 --> 13:59.420
Strangely, no.

14:03.290 --> 14:05.120
-(sighs)
-Does it look too formal?

14:05.120 --> 14:08.120
I want it to look formal,
kind of like as a joke,
you know?

14:08.120 --> 14:11.170
It's my first time,
so I went overboard.

14:11.170 --> 14:12.670
That's why I put out
the shrimp forks.

14:12.670 --> 14:15.380
-(chuckles)
-Maybe he won't get it.

14:15.380 --> 14:17.420
Okay, let's lose
the shrimp forks.

14:18.750 --> 14:20.330
I guess I am
a little nervous.

14:20.330 --> 14:21.620
It's gonna work out, right?

14:21.620 --> 14:24.210
Yes, it's going
to work out perfectly.

14:24.210 --> 14:26.080
(knocks on door)

14:26.080 --> 14:27.620
And he's even on time.

14:29.120 --> 14:30.380
Let's not
keep him waiting.

14:31.540 --> 14:32.670
(sighs)

14:34.210 --> 14:35.460
-Mmm.
-Oh, yeah.

14:35.460 --> 14:36.460
(sighs)

14:38.460 --> 14:39.500
Hi.

14:40.670 --> 14:42.330
-(door closes)
-Hi.

14:44.880 --> 14:46.170
I've got
a little surprise.

14:46.170 --> 14:49.120
-We do too.
-I'll go first.

14:50.330 --> 14:51.500
-Man: Hey!
-Man 2: What's up?

14:51.500 --> 14:52.830
Man 3: Hey!

14:52.830 --> 14:54.540
-(Bex sighs)
-(Bowie chuckles)

14:54.540 --> 14:56.250
What's going on?

14:56.250 --> 14:59.330
The Renaissance Boys!
Surprise!

15:01.380 --> 15:02.620
What's your surprise?

15:10.080 --> 15:11.420
-Bex, this is Micah...
-Hi.

15:11.420 --> 15:12.580
-...Guthrie...
-Hey.

15:12.580 --> 15:14.580
-...and Rafe.
-Hey.

15:14.580 --> 15:16.170
Oh, this is Andi.
This is my daughter.

15:16.170 --> 15:20.210
Oh, it is so
very nice to meet you.
Nice to meet both of you.

15:20.210 --> 15:23.670
Wow. A whole rock band.

15:24.670 --> 15:26.210
Are they staying
for dinner?

15:26.210 --> 15:27.580
Yeah, I didn't know they
were coming by.

15:27.580 --> 15:28.750
They just kinda showed up.

15:28.750 --> 15:31.290
If we are intruding,
you just send us
on our way.

15:31.290 --> 15:34.040
-Oh...
-Not at all.

15:34.040 --> 15:35.620
What a thrill.

15:35.620 --> 15:38.330
Make yourselves comfortable.
Do you want anything to drink?

15:38.330 --> 15:39.620
Oh, I'll take care of 'em.

15:40.790 --> 15:41.830
Thanks.

15:41.830 --> 15:43.420
Huh!

15:43.420 --> 15:45.170
(nervous chuckle)

15:47.460 --> 15:49.790
-What do we do?
-Should we still go
through with it?

15:49.790 --> 15:51.580
I'm asking you.

15:53.420 --> 15:55.580
-I say yes.
-I say yes too.

15:55.580 --> 15:58.420
It could be a single
on their next album.

15:58.420 --> 15:59.330
(giggles)

16:02.000 --> 16:04.580
Cyrus: I mean,
the good part about this is
that we can all be friends now.

16:04.580 --> 16:06.580
-Right?
-TJ: I can.

16:06.580 --> 16:09.420
'Cause I've never done
anything horrible to you,

16:09.420 --> 16:12.210
-like what
you've done to me.
-Valid point.

16:13.540 --> 16:16.380
I could forgive you.
I think I already have.

16:17.380 --> 16:20.210
I just don't know
if we could ever be friends.

16:20.210 --> 16:23.790
-What if he apologized?
-It would have to be like
the best apology ever.

16:25.120 --> 16:28.580
-I mean,
give it a shot.
-(sighs)

16:32.380 --> 16:35.290
♪ If you're
looking for a captain,
her name's Buffy Driscoll ♪

16:35.290 --> 16:37.790
♪ Gonna start a girls' team
and make that ish official ♪

16:37.790 --> 16:40.460
♪ Steal your ball so fast,
that you'll wanna
bring police in ♪

16:40.460 --> 16:43.120
♪ Tell them it got taken
like she's Liam Neeson ♪

16:43.120 --> 16:45.620
♪ The slickest,
sickest, quickest,
the most wicked in the world ♪

16:45.620 --> 16:46.960
♪ Used to hate her,
instigate her ♪

16:46.960 --> 16:48.290
♪ Told her,
"Good job for a girl" ♪

16:48.290 --> 16:49.500
♪ I didn't want to hear it ♪

16:49.500 --> 16:51.210
♪ But she taught me
all the same ♪

16:51.210 --> 16:52.330
♪ If you wanna
change the world ♪

16:52.330 --> 16:53.880
♪ Then you gotta
change the game ♪

16:56.750 --> 16:58.380
Was that
the best apology ever?

16:58.380 --> 17:01.750
(chuckles)
I think maybe it was.

17:03.080 --> 17:06.170
-So, we're good?
-Yeah, I think we are.

17:06.170 --> 17:08.880
Cool. I'll see you
around then.

17:13.380 --> 17:15.290
I am so confused
right now.

17:16.380 --> 17:17.830
You think
you're confused?

17:17.830 --> 17:20.170
Take a walk
through my head.

17:22.460 --> 17:25.250
♪ ♪

17:33.080 --> 17:34.920
You think
you know someone.

17:34.920 --> 17:37.210
Until you find out
that you don't.

17:39.420 --> 17:42.920
-(laughter)
-Rafe: See, I did not fall
off the stage,

17:42.920 --> 17:44.540
that was
a deliberate dive.

17:44.540 --> 17:46.210
Right, right, right.
Onto the ground.

17:46.210 --> 17:50.170
-Okay.
-(laughter)

17:51.580 --> 17:53.540
-What's so funny?
-Mom!

17:53.540 --> 17:55.000
What are you doing here?

17:55.000 --> 17:57.670
I live here.
What are you doing here?

17:57.670 --> 18:00.420
Clearly having a party
while I'm out.

18:00.420 --> 18:05.000
-One of your signature moves.
-Hey, why don't we take this
into the kitchen?

18:05.000 --> 18:07.500
-Yeah.
-Come on.

18:07.500 --> 18:09.330
Oh, um, just the girls.

18:13.670 --> 18:17.000
Let me just say,
I am angry and I am hurt.

18:17.000 --> 18:21.380
You say I need to get away.
You trick me into leaving
my own home!

18:21.380 --> 18:24.380
I don't like being away!
It's not fun being away.

18:24.380 --> 18:26.880
And, as usual,
you weren't doing
anything for me,

18:26.880 --> 18:28.620
you were doing something
for yourself!

18:28.620 --> 18:31.830
Andi and I are going
to propose to Bowie.

18:34.040 --> 18:36.830
Well, why are you in here
talking to me? Get out there!

18:36.830 --> 18:38.540
Okay, I guess
it's time for cake.

18:41.420 --> 18:44.500
-Let's go.
-Wait, why do
you need cake?

18:47.420 --> 18:49.380
I just wanna
let you know

18:49.380 --> 18:50.880
the cake was
Andi's idea.

18:52.380 --> 18:53.620
Okay.

18:53.620 --> 18:55.670
You'll get
what I mean later.

18:55.670 --> 18:59.500
Before you do that,
I wonder if I could
say something.

18:59.500 --> 19:01.420
-By all means.
-First of all,

19:01.420 --> 19:03.920
thank you so much
for this magnificent feast.

19:03.920 --> 19:06.670
Bowie's lead us
to believe that you exist
mainly on pizza.

19:06.670 --> 19:08.880
Well, emotionally,
that is true.

19:08.880 --> 19:11.290
Now, there is something
I want to say to Bowie.

19:13.540 --> 19:16.710
Bowie, we didn't just
happen to be passing
through town.

19:16.710 --> 19:19.670
We came here
especially to see you.

19:21.420 --> 19:23.620
Man, you're kinda
freaking me out here.

19:23.620 --> 19:26.420
We have a question
we wanna ask you.

19:26.420 --> 19:29.380
Dude! (chuckles)
You seem like you're about
to propose or something.

19:33.250 --> 19:35.670
-What is happening?
-What is happening?

19:35.670 --> 19:38.120
-What is happening?
-You've gotta move
quickly with this guy.

19:38.120 --> 19:39.380
He's very popular.

19:40.500 --> 19:43.000
Bowie, your boys need you.

19:43.000 --> 19:44.710
We got our first
international tour.

19:44.710 --> 19:47.580
-(shouts) For real?
-Yes!

19:47.580 --> 19:50.670
-(mimics explosion)
That is my brain right now!
-(laughter)

19:50.670 --> 19:52.710
(mimics gunfire)

19:52.710 --> 19:57.580
Bowie Quinn, would you do us
the honor of becoming
our rhythm guitarist?

19:57.580 --> 19:59.620
What?

19:59.620 --> 20:02.170
Please say yes and make us
the happiest band in the world.

20:04.880 --> 20:06.580
Guys...

20:06.580 --> 20:09.790
remember, I--
I just met my daughter.

20:11.460 --> 20:14.080
Six months, that's--
that's all we're asking.
Just for the tour.

20:18.580 --> 20:23.080
Ah. I am so touched,
and I am so happy... for you,

20:23.080 --> 20:24.830
but I can't.

20:27.170 --> 20:29.040
Yes, you can.

20:29.040 --> 20:31.830
This is
your lifelong dream,
Bowie, coming true.

20:33.750 --> 20:38.170
-Can I think about it?
-Sure, for a couple of hours,

20:38.170 --> 20:40.710
'cause we're
driving to New York.
Got a 6:00 a.m. flight.

20:40.710 --> 20:42.170
(laughs)

20:43.670 --> 20:45.040
We should talk.

20:46.670 --> 20:47.670
Yeah.

20:51.420 --> 20:53.920
-What do we do now?
-He has to go on this tour.

20:53.920 --> 20:56.880
-I agree.
-He can't give up
this opportunity for me.

20:56.880 --> 20:59.960
I don't want him to.
He needs to know that.

20:59.960 --> 21:03.500
-I agree.
-I'm so excited for him.

21:03.500 --> 21:06.750
Me too, but it means
we can't propose.

21:06.750 --> 21:09.380
What? Why not?

21:09.380 --> 21:11.620
If we propose,
then he won't go.

21:11.620 --> 21:14.290
He won't want to leave us.
That's how he is.

21:14.290 --> 21:17.420
-You know that's how he is.
-He'll go if we tell him
that it's okay,

21:17.420 --> 21:20.580
-that we want him to go.
-You can't let Bowie
go on this tour.

21:20.580 --> 21:23.250
Six months
around the world
with a rock band?

21:23.250 --> 21:25.620
He met somebody working
at a local plant nursery.

21:25.620 --> 21:28.250
That's why we need
to propose.

21:28.250 --> 21:31.540
Let's just lock the man down
and let him decide
if he wants to go.

21:31.540 --> 21:33.380
And he'll decide not to,

21:33.380 --> 21:35.460
and that's always
gonna be on us.

21:35.460 --> 21:36.830
I know him
better than you.

21:36.830 --> 21:38.750
And I clearly have
more faith in him than you.

21:38.750 --> 21:41.670
Well, we can't propose
if one of us doesn't want to.

21:41.670 --> 21:44.040
You can't start
making up rules now!

21:44.040 --> 21:46.580
-Bowie:
Okay if we cut the cake?
-Andi and Bex: No!

21:46.580 --> 21:49.710
-Why can't he cut the cake?
-Because the ring
is in the cake,

21:49.710 --> 21:51.500
-and he can't find it.
-Yes, he can!

21:51.500 --> 21:52.960
The ring is
in the cake?

21:52.960 --> 21:54.330
That's more
of a choking hazard

21:54.330 --> 21:57.000
than this toothpick
I found sticking out of it.

21:57.000 --> 21:58.920
-Mom!
-What?

21:58.920 --> 22:00.830
-What'd I do?
-Andi: What are
you gonna do?

22:00.830 --> 22:02.580
Celia:
I thought
I was helping!

22:03.880 --> 22:06.670
-(sighs)
-I guess it's up
to the universe now.

22:06.670 --> 22:08.000
It's out
of our hands.

22:09.170 --> 22:10.250
No, it isn't.

22:10.250 --> 22:12.830
-What are you doing?
-What?

22:12.830 --> 22:15.670
This is a crumble cake.
This is how it's supposed
to be served.

22:15.670 --> 22:18.580
-Oh, uh, let me
help you with that.
-Yeah.

22:19.620 --> 22:22.750
-What are you doing?
-I'm making crumbles.

22:22.750 --> 22:25.920
Be advised, none of them
washed their hands.

22:27.330 --> 22:29.580
Whoa. Dude,
what is this?

22:29.580 --> 22:31.500
♪ All I need from you
is a second chance ♪

22:31.500 --> 22:33.210
♪ A second chance ♪

22:33.210 --> 22:35.210
♪ A second chance ♪

22:35.210 --> 22:38.170
♪ To show that I mean it ♪

22:38.170 --> 22:41.790
♪ Time is ticking,
make it last ♪

22:41.790 --> 22:43.540
Do you wanna tell him?

22:43.540 --> 22:44.920
I thought
you wanted
to tell him.

22:44.920 --> 22:47.000
-I'll tell him.
-Andi and Bex:
No, you won't.

22:47.000 --> 22:48.960
Somebody tell me something.

22:50.170 --> 22:51.210
Um...

22:53.040 --> 22:54.040
Um...

22:55.790 --> 22:57.330
Bowie:
"Um..."?

23:00.210 --> 23:03.210
♪ Life is upside down ♪

23:03.210 --> 23:06.250
♪ But any way it go-o-oes ♪

23:06.250 --> 23:08.670
♪ I'll work it out ♪

23:08.670 --> 23:12.080
♪ Oh, oh, here we go ♪

23:12.080 --> 23:13.250
(camera clicks)

23:13.250 --> 23:14.290
♪ One, two, three! ♪

23:14.290 --> 23:16.290
♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

23:16.290 --> 23:18.750
♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪

23:18.750 --> 23:21.000
♪ There ain't no map to follow

23:21.000 --> 23:23.460
♪ But I'm with you
all the way ♪

23:23.460 --> 23:24.670
(camera clicking)

23:24.670 --> 23:26.120
♪ All the way ♪
